00:20:09,864 --> 00:20:11,164
♪ There's a camera rolling
on her hack ♪

513
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:12,549
Darling, you've arrived!

514
00:20:12,551 --> 00:20:13,633
I'll say.

515
00:20:13,635 --> 00:20:15,552
- Oh!
- Today has been absolute chaos.

516
00:20:15,554 --> 00:20:17,387
Maybe these earrings.

517
00:20:17,389 --> 00:20:18,705
You say that like it's a good thing.

518
00:20:18,707 --> 00:20:21,341
Honey, I don't just thrive
in chaos. I love it.

519
00:20:21,343 --> 00:20:23,727
The moment where all is lost is
the moment I wanna live in,

520
00:20:23,729 --> 00:20:26,713
because <i>that</i> is where creativity lives.

521
00:20:26,715 --> 00:20:27,847
It inspires.

522
00:20:27,849 --> 00:20:28,982
<i>I wondered if that was true</i>

523
00:20:28,984 --> 00:20:30,600
<i>or just the lie we tell ourselves.</i>

524
00:20:30,602 --> 00:20:31,718
Perfect.

525
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:35,054
Now give me that bag.
It deserves its moment.

526
00:20:35,056 --> 00:20:37,107
♪ Girls on film ♪ on film

527
00:20:37,109 --> 00:20:39,192
(exhales deeply)

528
00:20:40,494 --> 00:20:41,745
(Camera shutter clicks)

529
00:20:41,747 --> 00:20:43,663
♪ girls on film

530
00:20:43,665 --> 00:20:44,998
♪ two minutes later

531
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,534
♪ girls on film ♪ on film

532
00:20:47,536 --> 00:20:49,035
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>

533
00:20:49,037 --> 00:20:51,421
<i>One night, I wrote my name
on my mother's bag</i>

534
00:20:51,423 --> 00:20:52,905
<i>in attempt to salvage it,</i>

535
00:20:52,907 --> 00:20:56,376
<i>and now here I was, holding a zebra</i>

536
00:20:56,378 --> 00:20:57,594
<i>and watching my purse be photographed</i>

537
00:20:57,596 --> 00:20:59,129
<i>for "Interview" magazine.</i>

538
00:20:59,131 --> 00:21:01,914
<i>(Violent Femmes'
"Blister In The Sun" playing)</i>

539
00:21:01,916 --> 00:21:04,217
Thank you.
This is a dream come true.

540
00:21:04,219 --> 00:21:05,552
And to think,
you almost missed all this

541
00:21:05,554 --> 00:21:08,121
because of some boring work thing.

542
00:21:08,123 --> 00:21:09,723
Oh, no. Work.

543
00:21:09,725 --> 00:21:12,442
I have to go.
I have to get back.

544
00:21:12,444 --> 00:21:14,394
Here, uh, take this zebra.

545
00:21:14,396 --> 00:21:17,430
(Scoffs) Wait. You're such
a mystery, always dashing off.

546
00:21:17,432 --> 00:21:18,898
So exciting.

547
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:20,784
How will I get your purse back?

548
00:21:20,786 --> 00:21:22,285
Uh, I'll call you.

549
00:21:22,287 --> 00:21:23,453
Okay.

550
00:21:23,455 --> 00:21:24,771
Bye. Mwah!

551
00:21:24,773 --> 00:21:26,406
Oh, Carrie, wait!

552
00:21:26,408 --> 00:21:28,441
<i>♪ Big hands, I know you're the one ♪</i>

553
00:21:28,443 --> 00:21:32,295
I want you to have this.
It's Dior. It's one-of-a-kind.

554
00:21:32,297 --> 00:21:33,463
I can't take that.

555
00:21:33,465 --> 00:21:36,049
Oh, of course you can.
You deserve it.

556
00:21:36,051 --> 00:21:37,667
You're one-of-a-kind.

557
00:21:37,669 --> 00:21:41,254
You don't believe it,
but one day you will.

558
00:21:41,256 --> 00:21:43,289
How will I ever
believe that? (Chuckles)

559
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:44,591
You know the fairy tale Pinocchio?

560
00:21:44,593 --> 00:21:46,092
Yeah.
Well, that little puppet was

561
00:21:46,094 --> 00:21:49,312
a pretend boy who became real
because he believed it.

562
00:21:49,314 --> 00:21:51,731
Actually, Pinocchio
could only become real

563
00:21:51,733 --> 00:21:54,100
if he told the truth, and he couldn't.

564
00:21:54,102 --> 00:21:55,602
Okay, well...

565
00:21:55,604 --> 00:21:58,271
Then not that story.
(Laughs)

566
00:21:58,273 --> 00:22:00,607
The point is, sometimes you have
to fake it to make it.

567
00:22:00,609 --> 00:22:04,477
After a while,
what's fake becomes truth.

568
00:22:05,446 --> 00:22:07,247
<i>The only thing that would be true</i>

569
00:22:07,249 --> 00:22:08,665
<i>if I didn't get back and fast</i>

570
00:22:08,667 --> 00:22:10,583
<i>was how much trouble
I was going to be in...</i>

571
00:22:10,585 --> 00:22:12,752
♪ let me go on

572
00:22:12,754 --> 00:22:15,121
<i>and I knew time was running out for me.</i>

573
00:22:15,123 --> 00:22:18,174
♪ let me go on

574
00:22:18,176 --> 00:22:21,010
♪ big hands, I know you're the one ♪

575
00:22:35,359 --> 00:22:37,977
<i>Somehow, I had done it.</i>

576
00:22:37,979 --> 00:22:39,395
<i>Maybe Larissa was right.</i>

577
00:22:39,397 --> 00:22:44,150
<i>From chaos, even the impossible
can become possible,</i>

578
00:22:44,152 --> 00:22:46,653
<i>and I had made it happen.</i>

579
00:22:47,988 --> 00:22:50,089
<i>Except... I hadn't.</i>

580
00:22:50,091 --> 00:22:52,119
(Sighs)

581
00:22:58,629 --> 00:22:59,796
You're an hour and a half late.

582
00:22:59,798 --> 00:23:02,849
- I...
- Can explain? Maybe <i>I</i> should explain.

583
00:23:02,851 --> 00:23:04,767
I'm the person
who signs that little sheet

584
00:23:04,769 --> 00:23:06,969
that gets you credit
for this internship.

585
00:23:06,971 --> 00:23:09,389
- But...
- But you think you're young and cute,

586
00:23:09,391 --> 00:23:10,589
and because your dad is friends

587
00:23:10,591 --> 00:23:12,925
with Harlan silver,
one of the partners here,

588
00:23:12,927 --> 00:23:14,593
you're not accountable.

589
00:23:14,595 --> 00:23:17,196
No. I know I am.

590
00:23:17,198 --> 00:23:18,764
These are the binders
that are already done.

591
00:23:18,766 --> 00:23:20,016
Well, 50 of them.

592
00:23:20,018 --> 00:23:22,268
I still have the last ten to do
this afternoon.

593
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:23,936
When the printer realized
their mistake,

594
00:23:23,938 --> 00:23:26,656
they offered to collate them
free of charge.

595
00:23:26,658 --> 00:23:29,025
Uh, and here's the Constantine case.

596
00:23:29,027 --> 00:23:30,126
Oh, cases.

597
00:23:30,128 --> 00:23:31,461
There were two different Constantines,

598
00:23:31,463 --> 00:23:33,296
so I brought them both just to be safe.

599
00:23:33,298 --> 00:23:35,581
<i>It was gonna take
more than just fake confidence</i>

600
00:23:35,583 --> 00:23:37,133
<i>to get me through this.</i>

601
00:23:37,135 --> 00:23:38,935
And, um...
(Bag rustles)

602
00:23:38,937 --> 00:23:41,087
Here.
What is that?

603
00:23:41,089 --> 00:23:43,556
It's a scarf.

604
00:23:43,558 --> 00:23:45,975
I know you have
something special tonight,

605
00:23:45,977 --> 00:23:49,011
so I thought you might like this.

606
00:23:51,515 --> 00:23:53,399
I couldn't take that.

607
00:23:53,401 --> 00:23:55,634
I bought it for you.

608
00:24:00,491 --> 00:24:02,825
How much do I owe you?

609
00:24:02,827 --> 00:24:05,278
I got it in the bargain bin.

610
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:08,498
You can buy me a bagel
or something one morning.

611
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:12,318
Oh, and I, uh, left
your Chinese food on your desk.

612
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:14,303
And I got you extra pancakes.

613
00:24:14,305 --> 00:24:16,539
(Inhales deeply) Well, thank you.

614
00:24:16,541 --> 00:24:18,508
Now get back to work.

615
00:24:18,510 --> 00:24:19,992
Those binders aren't gonna
bind themselves.

616
00:24:19,994 --> 00:24:23,262
And if you screw up again
or disobey me,

617
00:24:23,264 --> 00:24:24,663
this internship's over.

618
00:24:28,719 --> 00:24:30,136
<i>The scarf was gone,</i>

619
00:24:30,138 --> 00:24:33,523
<i>but at least for now my life
here in Manhattan as safe.</i>

620
00:24:33,525 --> 00:24:34,724
<i>I figured a little lie</i>

621
00:24:34,726 --> 00:24:38,161
<i>about a one-of-a-kind scarf
was worth it.</i>

622
00:24:39,863 --> 00:24:40,897
(Donna laughs)

623
00:24:40,899 --> 00:24:42,398
<i>Meanwhile, the mouse was wondering</i>

624
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,700
<i>just what to tell me
about what she was seeing.</i>

625
00:24:44,702 --> 00:24:48,521
Oh! Mouse!
Mouse, come here.

626
00:24:50,324 --> 00:24:52,074
Hey.

627
00:24:52,076 --> 00:24:53,359
Hey.

628
00:24:53,361 --> 00:24:56,128
You look <i>so</i> cute today.
Doesn't she? So cute.

629
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:57,696
Sure.

630
00:24:57,698 --> 00:24:59,365
Yeah.

631
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:00,533
- Sure.
- Thanks.

632
00:25:00,535 --> 00:25:01,701
Well, I'm glad you showed up.

633
00:25:01,703 --> 00:25:04,170
I actually have to head off
to a massage, so...

634
00:25:04,172 --> 00:25:06,105
Sebastian here has just
been talking my ear off.

635
00:25:06,107 --> 00:25:08,341
That's me. The chatty type.

636
00:25:08,343 --> 00:25:10,059
(Laughs) You're so funny.

637
00:25:10,061 --> 00:25:12,812
Well, I will see you guys later.

638
00:25:12,814 --> 00:25:15,598
Don't miss me too much.

639
00:25:29,329 --> 00:25:31,497
It sucks you're not coming
to the video class tomorrow.

640
00:25:31,499 --> 00:25:34,917
It's gonna be so rad.
We're making a music video.

641
00:25:34,919 --> 00:25:38,504
I can't. I promised Carrie
I'd hang with her at the pool.

642
00:25:38,506 --> 00:25:39,755
I thought you hated her.

643
00:25:39,757 --> 00:25:43,709
She's not so bad.
I kinda feel sorry for her.

644
00:25:43,711 --> 00:25:46,128
It feels like she needs me,
so I don't wanna disappoint her.

645
00:25:46,130 --> 00:25:48,464
The only time my sister
even acknowledges me

646
00:25:48,466 --> 00:25:50,049
is when she knows
I took a message for her

647
00:25:50,051 --> 00:25:52,718
from one of her lame boyfriends.

648
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:53,986
It's cool you and Carrie
like to hang out.

649
00:25:53,988 --> 00:25:56,188
Yeah. Whatever.
No big deal.

650
00:25:56,190 --> 00:26:00,409
♪

651
00:26:00,411 --> 00:26:03,095
This is from the photo shoot.
Larissa gave it to me.

652
00:26:03,097 --> 00:26:04,397
You might be the coolest person I know.

653
00:26:04,399 --> 00:26:07,934
Stop. As we both know,
I am a... (Whispers) Loser.

654
00:26:07,936 --> 00:26:09,535
Mnh-mnh. That's not what
Larissa thinks.

655
00:26:09,537 --> 00:26:11,487
It's weird. After Larissa
told me to fake it,

656
00:26:11,489 --> 00:26:12,922
I had to go back to my office

657
00:26:12,924 --> 00:26:15,124
and pretend I wasn't terrified
of bitchy Barbara.

658
00:26:15,126 --> 00:26:18,794
You know what? It worked.
It saved me from being fired.

659
00:26:18,796 --> 00:26:19,962
Hmm.

660
00:26:19,964 --> 00:26:23,082
Maybe it is that simple,
just believing it.

661
00:26:23,084 --> 00:26:24,584
Yeah.

662
00:26:24,586 --> 00:26:28,387
I should tell myself
I'm ready... with Maggie.

663
00:26:28,389 --> 00:26:29,755
Are you?

664
00:26:29,757 --> 00:26:32,725
(Sighs deeply) I don't know
what I'm waiting for.

665
00:26:32,727 --> 00:26:34,560
And it's important to her.

666
00:26:34,562 --> 00:26:36,295
(Inhales deeply)

667
00:26:36,297 --> 00:26:38,598
I'm gonna surprise her
tomorrow after school.

668
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,316
I guess.

669
00:26:40,318 --> 00:26:42,101
But, Walt...
(Door closes)

670
00:26:43,270 --> 00:26:45,404
Mouse.
What are you doing here?

671
00:26:45,406 --> 00:26:47,406
I guess all your friends
really wanted to make sure

672
00:26:47,408 --> 00:26:48,858
you got your homework.

673
00:26:48,860 --> 00:26:51,277
Okay, you guys can only stay
here for a little while longer.

674
00:26:51,279 --> 00:26:53,746
All right? Carrie is
still grounded, after all.

675
00:26:53,748 --> 00:26:55,114
Leaving in five.

676
00:26:56,617 --> 00:26:59,085
I change my vote on Sebastian.

677
00:26:59,087 --> 00:27:00,486
What are you talking about?

678
00:27:00,488 --> 00:27:01,921
Go for it.

679
00:27:01,923 --> 00:27:04,624
You cannot let that two-faced,
big-lipped bitch get him.

680
00:27:04,626 --> 00:27:06,359
She's kind of an evil genius.

681
00:27:06,361 --> 00:27:09,261
I completely underestimated her.

682
00:27:09,263 --> 00:27:10,963
She called me cute

683
00:27:10,965 --> 00:27:13,115
and said that she was happy to see me

684
00:27:13,117 --> 00:27:14,717
in front of Sebastian.

685
00:27:14,719 --> 00:27:17,153
She actually seemed nice.

686
00:27:17,155 --> 00:27:18,554
Donna.

687
00:27:18,556 --> 00:27:19,805
Nice.

688
00:27:19,807 --> 00:27:21,774
Okay, that is terrifying.

689
00:27:21,776 --> 00:27:24,744
(Chuckles) You better move, and fast.

690
00:27:32,119 --> 00:27:34,120
You wanna meet at the swim club today?

691
00:27:34,122 --> 00:27:36,288
I thought you were grounded?

692
00:27:36,290 --> 00:27:39,208
That's for me to worry about.
So do you wanna meet or not?

693
00:27:39,210 --> 00:27:41,160
Of course.
Meet there at 4:30?

694
00:27:41,162 --> 00:27:42,828
Make it 4:00 and I'm yours.

695
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:44,163
I like the sound of that.

696
00:27:44,165 --> 00:27:46,640
Good. Don't be late.

697
00:27:58,192 --> 00:28:00,578
<i>Today was the day...</i>

698
00:28:02,297 --> 00:28:05,866
<i>I would</i> completely <i>disappoint Dorrit.</i>

699
00:28:05,868 --> 00:28:07,751
Dorrit.

700
00:28:07,753 --> 00:28:11,171
Why do you seem surprised to see me?

701
00:28:12,674 --> 00:28:13,807
So you're not mad?

702
00:28:13,809 --> 00:28:15,476
Of course not. I get it.

703
00:28:15,478 --> 00:28:17,978
(Sighs) Okay, so I'll see you
at home. You're okay walking?

704
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:19,930
Sure. No problem.

705
00:28:19,932 --> 00:28:22,066
We can hang when I get back.

706
00:28:23,068 --> 00:28:25,319
<i>I told myself that Dorrit was fine.</i>

707
00:28:25,321 --> 00:28:27,104
<i>I wasn't sure if I believed it,</i>

708
00:28:27,106 --> 00:28:29,273
<i>but I didn't have time to dwell on it.</i>

709
00:28:29,275 --> 00:28:31,609
<i>And while I hurried to get ready...</i>

710
00:28:31,611 --> 00:28:33,377
(Doorbell rings) <i>Walt waited...</i>

711
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:35,462
<i>For Maggie.</i>

712
00:28:43,088 --> 00:28:47,458
<i>Unfortunately,
Maggie hadn't waited for Walt.</i>

713
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:48,759
Oh, thank God it's you.

714
00:28:48,761 --> 00:28:50,427
Oh, I don't know who else it'd be.

715
00:28:50,429 --> 00:28:52,296
Well, see, my dad's
the chief of police,

716
00:28:52,298 --> 00:28:55,299
so he has this car with, like,
the lights and the siren thingy.

717
00:28:55,301 --> 00:28:56,934
You're such a smart-ass.

718
00:28:56,936 --> 00:28:58,135
Isn't that what you like about me?

719
00:28:58,137 --> 00:28:59,386
Come on. Get in.

720
00:28:59,388 --> 00:29:00,754
Thought you'd never ask.

721
00:29:02,774 --> 00:29:03,941
(Engine starts)

722
00:29:03,943 --> 00:29:07,094
<i>While Maggie was all bravado,</i>

723
00:29:07,096 --> 00:29:09,930
<i>I tried to fake I wasn't nervous</i>

724
00:29:09,932 --> 00:29:12,483
<i>but was doing a lousy job.</i>

725
00:29:24,796 --> 00:29:28,799
(Police radio chatter)

726
00:29:28,801 --> 00:29:29,833
I love how aggressive you are.

727
00:29:29,835 --> 00:29:31,251
I am not. Shut up.
(Laughs)

728
00:29:31,253 --> 00:29:33,304
That time at your parents' barbecue...

729
00:29:33,306 --> 00:29:35,089
I never thought of you
as anything more than a kid.

730
00:29:35,091 --> 00:29:37,057
You showed me.

731
00:29:37,059 --> 00:29:39,476
(Radio chatter continues)

732
00:29:41,896 --> 00:29:43,514
Oh.

733
00:29:43,516 --> 00:29:44,765
Well, I hate to break up the party,

734
00:29:44,767 --> 00:29:46,984
but we should probably get going.

735
00:29:46,986 --> 00:29:49,770
Hey, can you, um...

736
00:29:49,772 --> 00:29:51,772
Can you just lie with me?

737
00:29:51,774 --> 00:29:53,473
It's getting kinda late.

738
00:29:53,475 --> 00:29:55,326
Just for a minute or two.

739
00:29:55,328 --> 00:29:57,528
You just can't get enough, can you?

740
00:30:02,817 --> 00:30:04,451
<i>It was getting harder and harder</i>

741
00:30:04,453 --> 00:30:08,455
<i>for Maggie to lie to herself
that this was real intimacy.</i>

742
00:30:12,844 --> 00:30:14,345
- Hey, kiddo.
- Hey.

743
00:30:14,347 --> 00:30:17,297
You're home from the pool early.

744
00:30:17,299 --> 00:30:18,632
Everything okay?

745
00:30:18,634 --> 00:30:20,184
(Door slams)

746
00:30:24,889 --> 00:30:26,724
So you didn't think I'd be on time?

747
00:30:26,726 --> 00:30:30,027
I never said that. I was
just impressed that you are.

748
00:30:30,029 --> 00:30:32,312
I hate people who are late.

749
00:30:32,314 --> 00:30:34,615
My mom's always late.

750
00:30:34,617 --> 00:30:36,450
You'd think after 18 years
of being screamed at by my dad,

751
00:30:36,452 --> 00:30:38,452
she could have figured out
how to be on time.

752
00:30:38,454 --> 00:30:40,854
Yeah, but we ladies have
a lot more to do

753
00:30:40,856 --> 00:30:42,656
than you to get ready, you know?

754
00:30:42,658 --> 00:30:45,743
We've gotta pick an outfit
and do our makeup and hair.

755
00:30:45,745 --> 00:30:48,028
You don't need any of that.

756
00:30:48,030 --> 00:30:49,546
Don't lie.

757
00:30:49,548 --> 00:30:51,915
I'm not lying.

758
00:30:53,802 --> 00:30:57,337
I want you to kiss me.

759
00:30:57,339 --> 00:30:59,206
So kiss me.

760
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:04,678
(Door opens in distance)

761
00:31:07,315 --> 00:31:10,234
Carrie?

762
00:31:10,236 --> 00:31:13,161
<i>It looked like my lies
were catching up to me.</i>

763
00:31:19,027 --> 00:31:20,945
(Engine starts)

764
00:31:20,947 --> 00:31:22,363
Let's go, Carrie.

765
00:31:23,398 --> 00:31:26,016
Mr. Bradshaw?

766
00:31:26,018 --> 00:31:28,536
I want to apologize.
For corrupting my daughter?

767
00:31:28,538 --> 00:31:30,705
I asked him there.
It was my idea.

768
00:31:30,707 --> 00:31:34,242
But I said yes.
I-I apologize, sir.

769
00:31:34,244 --> 00:31:37,161
I'm Sebastian,
Mr. Bradshaw.

770
00:31:43,535 --> 00:31:45,219
That's a nice handshake.

771
00:31:45,221 --> 00:31:46,804
Thank you, sir.

772
00:31:46,806 --> 00:31:49,807
My grandfather taught me
the handshake makes the man.

773
00:31:49,809 --> 00:31:52,894
(Chuckles) Yeah, mine, too.

774
00:31:52,896 --> 00:31:54,879
What did you say your name was?

775
00:31:54,881 --> 00:31:56,848
Sebastian. Sebastian Kydd.

776
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:58,649
Garret's son?

777
00:31:58,651 --> 00:31:59,901
You know my dad?

778
00:31:59,903 --> 00:32:01,385
I do. Yeah.

779
00:32:01,387 --> 00:32:04,572
Now if, uh, you'll excuse us,
Sebastian, we have to get going.

780
00:32:04,574 --> 00:32:05,857
(Under breath) So I can be punished

781
00:32:05,859 --> 00:32:07,391
for the rest of my life.

782
00:32:07,393 --> 00:32:10,178
(Car door closes)

783
00:32:10,180 --> 00:32:12,280
(Engine starts)

784
00:32:21,924 --> 00:32:23,090
Walt.

785
00:32:23,092 --> 00:32:25,343
(Dog barking in distance)
What are you doing here?

786
00:32:25,345 --> 00:32:28,012
Waiting for you.

787
00:32:28,014 --> 00:32:30,131
For how long?

788
00:32:30,133 --> 00:32:31,415
The last four hours.

789
00:32:31,417 --> 00:32:33,601
You waited here all that time?

790
00:32:35,103 --> 00:32:37,104
I came here

791
00:32:37,106 --> 00:32:38,973
because I thought I was ready.

792
00:32:40,225 --> 00:32:42,143
That tonight was it.

793
00:32:43,695 --> 00:32:46,063
But...

794
00:32:46,065 --> 00:32:49,033
The longer I waited
and wondered where you were...

795
00:32:49,035 --> 00:32:51,235
I wasn't with anyone, I swear.

796
00:32:51,237 --> 00:32:53,588
It doesn't matter.

797
00:32:55,407 --> 00:32:56,490
That's weird, right?

798
00:32:56,492 --> 00:32:59,010
That I wouldn't care.

799
00:32:59,012 --> 00:33:02,046
I don't know. Maybe you're not
the jealous type.

800
00:33:02,048 --> 00:33:03,998
(Sighs deeply)

801
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:06,116
I wanted to believe
that I was in love with you

802
00:33:06,118 --> 00:33:07,702
in the way that it matters.

803
00:33:07,704 --> 00:33:10,621
But the longer I stood here,

804
00:33:10,623 --> 00:33:13,674
I realized I wasn't.

805
00:33:13,676 --> 00:33:15,726
What are you saying?

806
00:33:15,728 --> 00:33:18,479
I think we should break up.

807
00:33:18,481 --> 00:33:20,898
(Voice breaks) Um, d-did I do
something? Because I can change.

808
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:23,568
We can make it work.
It's not you. You're perfect.

809
00:33:23,570 --> 00:33:24,986
Then why don't you love me?

810
00:33:24,988 --> 00:33:26,737
(Sighs) Mags, I do.

811
00:33:26,739 --> 00:33:28,406
(Crying)

812
00:33:28,408 --> 00:33:30,391
Just...

813
00:33:30,393 --> 00:33:31,609
Not in that way.

814
00:33:31,611 --> 00:33:33,995
(Continues crying)

815
00:33:33,997 --> 00:33:37,314
But I'll always be here for you.

816
00:33:37,316 --> 00:33:39,116
Always.

817
00:33:40,986 --> 00:33:42,870
(Whispers) I'm sorry.

818
00:33:47,492 --> 00:33:51,045
<i>And for the first time,
Walt wasn't lying.</i>

819
00:33:51,047 --> 00:33:55,383
<i>It was hard, but at least
it was the truth.</i>

820
00:34:03,942 --> 00:34:07,278
Morning, daddy.
I made you breakfast.

821
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:10,448
Strawberry with frosting.
Your favorite.

822
00:34:10,450 --> 00:34:12,516
And your coffee.

823
00:34:12,518 --> 00:34:14,184
(Coffee pouring) Yeah, buttering me up

824
00:34:14,186 --> 00:34:16,320
isn't gonna change
what happened last night.

825
00:34:16,322 --> 00:34:18,623
Will I be able to
leave the house before college?

826
00:34:18,625 --> 00:34:20,541
Your punishment is done today.

827
00:34:20,543 --> 00:34:23,794
I said two weeks,
and it's been two weeks.

828
00:34:23,796 --> 00:34:25,913
Is this a trick?
(Mug clatters)

829
00:34:25,915 --> 00:34:28,866
I'm not gonna lie to you.

830
00:34:28,868 --> 00:34:32,003
I never would've expected
this kind of behavior from you.

831
00:34:32,005 --> 00:34:33,754
I'm sorry.

832
00:34:33,756 --> 00:34:35,473
Just...

833
00:34:35,475 --> 00:34:37,925
Please know you <i>can</i> trust me.

834
00:34:37,927 --> 00:34:40,261
Can I? You lied to me.

835
00:34:40,263 --> 00:34:43,097
And I shouldn't have.

836
00:34:43,099 --> 00:34:44,849
I know that.

837
00:34:44,851 --> 00:34:47,101
(Sighs) Does it help that I feel awful?

838
00:34:47,103 --> 00:34:48,552
If Dorrit hadn't told me,

839
00:34:48,554 --> 00:34:50,905
I never would've even known
that you disobeyed me.

840
00:34:50,907 --> 00:34:52,723
I can't be with you all the time,

841
00:34:52,725 --> 00:34:54,391
but I have to trust that you're
gonna make the right choices,

842
00:34:54,393 --> 00:34:55,693
even when I'm not there.

843
00:34:55,695 --> 00:34:57,828
I need you to...

844
00:34:57,830 --> 00:34:59,163
Prove to me

845
00:34:59,165 --> 00:35:00,581
that you're the daughter
that I think you are.

846
00:35:00,583 --> 00:35:03,951
I will. I promise.

847
00:35:03,953 --> 00:35:07,237
Good. Because if you don't,
there will be consequences.

848
00:35:07,239 --> 00:35:08,422
I know.

849
00:35:08,424 --> 00:35:09,974
Like no more internship.

850
00:35:09,976 --> 00:35:12,426
Okay. I got it.

851
00:35:12,428 --> 00:35:14,762
No more screwups.

852
00:35:14,764 --> 00:35:16,931
Good.

853
00:35:19,084 --> 00:35:22,269
So... you're okay
if I go out tonight?

854
00:35:22,271 --> 00:35:25,940
Yeah, but not with that Sebastian.

855
00:35:25,942 --> 00:35:28,693
What?

856
00:35:28,695 --> 00:35:30,427
Wait, are you telling me I can't date?

857
00:35:30,429 --> 00:35:32,430
Because we're gonna have
a serious problem.

858
00:35:32,432 --> 00:35:34,648
No, I'm telling you that
you can't date <i>him.</i>

859
00:35:34,650 --> 00:35:37,952
I... know a little bit
about him and his family,

860
00:35:37,954 --> 00:35:40,821
and, uh, I'm telling you to stay away.

861
00:35:40,823 --> 00:35:42,373
Why?

862
00:35:42,375 --> 00:35:44,274
Because I said so.

863
00:35:44,276 --> 00:35:46,844
You expect me not to see
the cutest guy at school,

864
00:35:46,846 --> 00:35:48,746
and your reason is "because I said so"?

865
00:35:48,748 --> 00:35:51,115
Yeah.

866
00:35:54,503 --> 00:35:59,390
<i>Pinocchio was a puppet
that wanted to be a real boy.</i>

867
00:35:59,392 --> 00:36:01,258
<i>All he had to do was be truthful,</i>

868
00:36:01,260 --> 00:36:03,477
<i>and his wish would come true.</i>

869
00:36:03,479 --> 00:36:06,130
<i>And even then,
he couldn't help but lie.</i>

870
00:36:07,649 --> 00:36:10,134
<i>Doing the right thing is hard.</i>

871
00:36:10,136 --> 00:36:13,687
<i>Maybe because lying is often
easier than the truth.</i>

872
00:36:13,689 --> 00:36:18,142
<i>And sometimes it actually
gets you what you want.</i>

873
00:36:18,144 --> 00:36:20,494
<i>But at some point,
like Pinocchio's nose,</i>

874
00:36:20,496 --> 00:36:22,163
<i>the lies just keep growing</i>

875
00:36:22,165 --> 00:36:26,000
<i>until it's hard to tell
what's real and what's not.</i>

876
00:36:27,786 --> 00:36:30,671
<i>And we can either live
in that world of make-believe</i>

877
00:36:30,673 --> 00:36:31,789
<i>or face the truth</i>

878
00:36:31,791 --> 00:36:35,009
<i>and everything that comes with it.</i>

879
00:36:38,296 --> 00:36:41,882
(Clatter)

880
00:36:41,884 --> 00:36:44,552
Hey.

881
00:36:44,554 --> 00:36:45,803
I know you're mad.

882
00:36:45,805 --> 00:36:48,839
I'm not mad.

883
00:36:48,841 --> 00:36:50,191
Not at you.
(Sighs)

884
00:36:50,193 --> 00:36:53,727
At myself... (Sighs)
For blowing you off.

885
00:36:53,729 --> 00:36:55,546
That wasn't cool.

886
00:36:55,548 --> 00:36:57,064
No, it wasn't.

887
00:36:57,066 --> 00:36:58,199
I'm sorry.

888
00:36:58,201 --> 00:36:59,984
I was hoping to make it up to you.

889
00:36:59,986 --> 00:37:01,869
You wanna hang out?
We can make a night of it?

890
00:37:01,871 --> 00:37:04,221
I think, uh, mouse is coming over.

891
00:37:04,223 --> 00:37:06,440
Maybe watch "The Wall" or something?

892
00:37:06,442 --> 00:37:07,741
Are we gonna be stoned?

893
00:37:07,743 --> 00:37:09,693
No.

894
00:37:09,695 --> 00:37:11,862
Then I don't get it.
What's the point?

895
00:37:13,632 --> 00:37:15,349
I bought a bootlegged copy
of "Purple Rain."

896
00:37:15,351 --> 00:37:16,667
How'd you get that?

897
00:37:16,669 --> 00:37:18,836
I think it's better if you don't know.

898
00:37:18,838 --> 00:37:20,387
(Sighs) Huh.

899
00:37:20,389 --> 00:37:21,739
You're something, Dorrit.

900
00:37:21,741 --> 00:37:24,341
I know.

901
00:37:24,343 --> 00:37:25,676
(Doorbell rings)

902
00:37:25,678 --> 00:37:28,262
That's probably mouse now.

903
00:37:35,604 --> 00:37:36,904
Hey.

904
00:37:36,906 --> 00:37:40,024
Hey.

905
00:37:40,026 --> 00:37:42,359
So that was weird yesterday.

906
00:37:42,361 --> 00:37:45,896
Yeah. My dad's
really overprotective.

907
00:37:45,898 --> 00:37:47,832
You grounded for life?

908
00:37:47,834 --> 00:37:49,733
Uh, surprisingly, no.

909
00:37:49,735 --> 00:37:52,736
So you can hang out tonight?
We can go to the concert.

910
00:37:52,738 --> 00:37:54,588
Actually, I can't.

911
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:56,624
- Oh.
- It's not that I don't want to.

912
00:37:56,626 --> 00:37:58,042
I do. A lot.

913
00:37:58,044 --> 00:38:01,345
Uh... it's just, things have
been tense in my house.

914
00:38:01,347 --> 00:38:04,348
Yeah, it's fine, Bradshaw.

915
00:38:04,350 --> 00:38:07,101
You can't be that mad at me
since you called me "Bradshaw."

916
00:38:07,103 --> 00:38:08,969
Does it bother you?

917
00:38:08,971 --> 00:38:11,171
No. I like it.

918
00:38:11,173 --> 00:38:13,474
Okay then, Bradshaw.

919
00:38:13,476 --> 00:38:15,693
I'll see you on monday.

920
00:38:15,695 --> 00:38:17,695
Okay, Kydd.

921
00:38:17,697 --> 00:38:18,779
I'll see you then.

922
00:38:18,781 --> 00:38:20,197
<i>All along,</i>

923
00:38:20,199 --> 00:38:23,083
<i>I thought I was juggling
my new guy and my new city.</i>

924
00:38:23,085 --> 00:38:26,153
<i>In reality,
it was a lot more complicated.</i>

925
00:38:26,155 --> 00:38:30,824
<i>I would need to choose between
Sebastian and my dad.</i>

926
00:38:30,826 --> 00:38:32,877
(Sighs) Who was that?

927
00:38:32,879 --> 00:38:35,412
Um, door-to-door salesman.

928
00:38:35,414 --> 00:38:38,515
Apparently, he thinks we need
more encyclopedias.

929
00:38:38,517 --> 00:38:39,616
I told him we didn't.

930
00:38:39,618 --> 00:38:42,586
(Chuckles) So what are you
gonna do tonight?

931
00:38:42,588 --> 00:38:43,954
Uh, mouse is on her way over.

932
00:38:43,956 --> 00:38:46,140
We're gonna watch "Purple Rain"
with Dorrit.

933
00:38:47,309 --> 00:38:48,625
<i>It turns out.</i>

934
00:38:48,627 --> 00:38:51,295
<i>I was a lot more like Pinocchio
than I thought.</i>

935
00:38:51,297 --> 00:38:53,764
I don't understand why
the movie looked like that.

936
00:38:53,766 --> 00:38:55,983
Did someone videotape it in a theater?

937
00:38:55,985 --> 00:38:57,067
Yes.

938
00:38:57,069 --> 00:38:59,403
It looked like crap.
Who would bother?

939
00:38:59,405 --> 00:39:00,571
Me.

940
00:39:00,573 --> 00:39:02,273
(Door closes)

941
00:39:02,275 --> 00:39:05,776
Hey. Um, I hope it's okay
I just let myself in.

942
00:39:05,778 --> 00:39:07,745
Mags, I thought you were
hanging out with Walt tonight?

943
00:39:07,747 --> 00:39:11,065
He... he broke up with me.

944
00:39:11,067 --> 00:39:13,167
Oh.

945
00:39:16,154 --> 00:39:17,755
I'm sorry.

946
00:39:17,757 --> 00:39:19,540
(Sniffles)

947
00:39:19,542 --> 00:39:21,491
(Carrie) It's okay.

948
00:39:23,261 --> 00:39:25,846
Dorrit, get in here.
Come on.

949
00:39:25,848 --> 00:39:27,047
(Chuckles)

950
00:39:27,049 --> 00:39:29,216
(Sniffles) Mmm.

951
00:39:31,219 --> 00:39:34,355
(Madness' "Our House" playing)

952
00:39:36,274 --> 00:39:37,942
Men are so damn complicated.

953
00:39:37,944 --> 00:39:39,509
Especially the dad-kind.

954
00:39:39,511 --> 00:39:41,178
I can second that.

955
00:39:41,180 --> 00:39:42,730
Or the ex-boyfriend-kind

956
00:39:42,732 --> 00:39:45,866
who calls you up after two weeks
and tells you they miss you.

957
00:39:45,868 --> 00:39:48,452
What? Seth called?

958
00:39:48,454 --> 00:39:49,570
What did you say?

959
00:39:49,572 --> 00:39:51,188
I said hi.

960
00:39:51,190 --> 00:39:53,273
So are you gonna take him back?

961
00:39:53,275 --> 00:39:55,876
(Sighs) I don't know.

962
00:39:57,162 --> 00:39:59,463
I just know I miss him.

963
00:39:59,465 --> 00:40:01,098
I miss Walt.

964
00:40:01,100 --> 00:40:03,050
I miss Sebastian.

965
00:40:03,052 --> 00:40:05,669
You guys are so lame.

966
00:40:08,089 --> 00:40:10,040
(Mouse, Carrie,
and Maggie laugh) Totally!

967
00:40:10,042 --> 00:40:11,925
Now give me one of those sandwiches.

968
00:40:11,927 --> 00:40:14,395
♪ In the middle of our street

969
00:40:14,397 --> 00:40:17,982
<i>Maybe the lies we had told
had complicated our lives.</i>

970
00:40:17,984 --> 00:40:19,149
<i>I couldn't deny the fact</i>

971
00:40:19,151 --> 00:40:20,851
<i>that we had created our own problems...</i>

972
00:40:20,853 --> 00:40:24,388
<i>Breakups, makeups, forbidden loves...</i>

973
00:40:24,390 --> 00:40:28,075
<i>It was hard to keep the fantasy
of what love could be alive.</i>

974
00:40:28,077 --> 00:40:30,911
<i>But the one thing I knew was true</i>

975
00:40:30,913 --> 00:40:33,230
<i>was that we were pretty lucky
to have each other</i>

976
00:40:33,232 --> 00:40:34,365
<i>to lean on through all of it.</i>

977
00:40:34,367 --> 00:40:35,953
♪ Our house

978
00:40:35,954 --> 00:40:38,401
♪ In the middle of our street
♪ Our house

